Generic single-database configuration with an async dialect.

This is a generic alembic configuration for use with the DeepSight backend.
It uses an async SQLAlchemy dialect with PostgreSQL.

To create a new migration:
```
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "description of changes"
```

To upgrade to the latest revision:
```
alembic upgrade head
```

To downgrade to a previous revision:
```
alembic downgrade -1  # downgrade one revision
alembic downgrade <revision>  # downgrade to specific revision
```

To get current revision:
```
alembic current
```

To get revision history:
```
alembic history